>Instal Java JDK 8
$java -version

openjdk version "1.8.0_252"
OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_252-8u252-b09-1ubuntu1-b09)
OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.252-b09, mixed mode)

>Run command
$ sudo apt update
$ sudo apt install openjdk-8-jdk openjdk-8-jre

>Run command to find jvm path in system
$ whereis jvm

>Install Android Studio and Gradle. Make sure to configure and install sdk and place gradle folder in Android Folder 

-https://gradle.org/install/
-https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-install-android-studio-on-ubuntu-18-04/

> Then install SDK in home folder
$ sudo apt-get install android-sdk
-https://stackoverflow.com/questions/34556884/how-to-install-android-sdk-on-ubuntu 

1. $ sudo gedit ~/.bashrc
Then place the below lines at the end
#Android
export ANDROID_HOME=/home/chetan/Android/Sdk
export PATH=$PATH:$ANDROID_HOME/tools
export PATH=$PATH:$ANDROID_HOME/platform-tools

#Java
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin

#Gradle	
export GRADLE_HOME=/home/chetan/android-studio/gradle-6.5.1
export PATH=$PATH:$GRADLE_HOME/bin

then close editor and enter command

$ source ~/.bashrc

2. $ sudo su
>enter password

	$ gedit /etc/environment
Then place the below lines

JAVA_HOME="/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64/"
export JAVA_HOME

ANDROID_HOME="/home/chetan/Android/Sdk/build-tools/30.0.0"

export GRADLE_HOME=/home/chetan/android-studio/gradle-6.5.1


then close editor and enter command

	$. /etc/environment

then enter these commands
$ export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin
$ export PATH=$PATH:$GRADLE_HOME/bin
$ export PATH=$PATH:$ANDROID_HOME

then check using $ echo $PATH OR $JAVA_HOME $GRADLE_HOME $ANDROID_HOME



For Liscensing SDK run command in Android Studio Folder
$ yes | ~/Android/Sdk/tools/bin/sdkmanager --licenses


